1
00:00:10,567 --> 00:00:13,033
<i> You have a problem.</i>

2
00:00:13,167 --> 00:00:15,867
<i> You need to consult a doctor.</i>

3
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:17,633
<i> What do you think of me?</i>

4
00:00:17,767 --> 00:00:18,533
<i> A crazy person?</i>

5
00:00:18,667 --> 00:00:19,400
<i> You!</i>

6
00:00:19,533 --> 00:00:20,800
<i> You're the crazy one!</i>

7
00:00:20,933 --> 00:00:21,600
<i> You!</i>

8
00:00:21,733 --> 00:00:23,767
<i> I want to forget Mom.</i>

9
00:00:23,900 --> 00:00:25,233
<i> Why aren't we leaving yet?</i>

10
00:00:25,367 --> 00:00:26,100
<i> Don't move.</i>

11
00:00:26,233 --> 00:00:27,667
<i> I'm looking for a woman.</i>

12
00:00:27,800 --> 00:00:29,400
<i> Did you see anyone?</i>

13
00:00:29,533 --> 00:00:30,033
<i> No.</i>

14
00:00:30,167 --> 00:00:31,633
<i> Emma! Emma!</i>

15
00:00:31,767 --> 00:00:34,033
<i>Can we please stop
talking about her?</i>

16
00:00:34,200 --> 00:00:38,133
<i>Artemis Pharmacy will launch
Ramirez Lab's new vitamins.</i>

17
00:00:38,267 --> 00:00:41,200
<i>That's where I'll haunt Jade
and seduce Danilo.</i>

18
00:00:41,333 --> 00:00:44,067
<i>Why would I let myself be
affected by someone with</i>

19
00:00:44,200 --> 00:00:46,133
<i> the same name as...</i>

20
00:00:46,267 --> 00:00:46,967
<i> Emma!</i>

21
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:51,000
<i>It seems like they're all
looking at us.</i>

22
00:00:51,133 --> 00:00:51,933
<i> At us?</i>

23
00:00:52,067 --> 00:00:53,700
<i> Maybe they're looking at you.</i>

24
00:00:53,833 --> 00:00:55,800
<i> You're the prettiest here.</i>

25
00:01:32,067 --> 00:01:33,567
Do you want to do a warm-up
over there?

26
00:01:41,500 --> 00:01:45,300
Maybe I shouldn't have put
a full makeup on.

27
00:01:45,433 --> 00:01:48,333
We became the center
of attention.

28
00:01:48,467 --> 00:01:49,533
Well...

29
00:01:49,667 --> 00:01:52,233
maybe for people who know you.

30
00:01:52,367 --> 00:01:56,767
Or if they come near you
or the place is well-lit.

31
00:01:56,900 --> 00:01:58,833
But you're safe.

32
00:02:01,267 --> 00:02:03,400
Have you seen them?

33
00:02:03,533 --> 00:02:04,967
Not yet.

34
00:02:06,967 --> 00:02:08,300
Marco.

35
00:02:08,433 --> 00:02:10,467
Have you seen the two?

36
00:02:10,600 --> 00:02:11,933
Twelve o'clock, Boss.

37
00:02:17,633 --> 00:02:18,867
Have you found them?

38
00:02:31,167 --> 00:02:33,233
<i> What should I do?</i>

39
00:02:33,367 --> 00:02:35,700
<i> Will I talk to him?</i>

40
00:02:35,833 --> 00:02:37,600
<i> But what do I tell him?</i>

41
00:02:42,433 --> 00:02:43,867
<i> Whatever.</i>

42
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:45,933
<i> I can't lose him as a friend.</i>

43
00:02:52,700 --> 00:02:54,100
Hi, Zayn!

44
00:02:55,767 --> 00:02:57,067
Can I join?

45
00:03:06,267 --> 00:03:07,600
How are you?

46
00:03:10,600 --> 00:03:12,000
Oh my gosh!

47
00:03:13,467 --> 00:03:14,833
Why?

48
00:03:14,967 --> 00:03:18,333
Oh my God, you're so handsome
today!

49
00:03:21,800 --> 00:03:25,167
<i>Sometimes,
you have to be strong, Mookie.</i>

50
00:03:25,300 --> 00:03:26,967
<i> You have to be brave.</i>

51
00:03:27,100 --> 00:03:29,300
<i> So what if Emma isn't here?</i>

52
00:03:29,433 --> 00:03:33,333
<i>Show them that you can live
alone.</i>

53
00:03:33,467 --> 00:03:36,000
<i> You must fight.</i>

54
00:03:36,133 --> 00:03:41,033
<i>You must always fight in
whatever circumstances.</i>

55
00:03:44,567 --> 00:03:45,667
<i> You can go to hell together!</i>

56
00:03:47,533 --> 00:03:51,300
<i>I might have pulled all her hair
out if you hadn't stopped me.</i>

57
00:03:51,433 --> 00:03:53,500
<i>You did the right thing, Mookie.</i>

58
00:03:53,633 --> 00:03:55,600
<i>It's just right that you fought.</i>

59
00:04:04,033 --> 00:04:05,233
Wait.

60
00:04:06,333 --> 00:04:13,167
Emma, tonight, you take your
power back.

61
00:04:13,300 --> 00:04:15,833
Your fight begins now.

62
00:04:15,967 --> 00:04:21,500
Remember, you are on
the offensive side.

63
00:04:21,633 --> 00:04:24,800
Don't let them get ahead of you.

64
00:04:24,933 --> 00:04:31,500
Most importantly, don't stray
from our plans.

65
00:04:31,667 --> 00:04:33,933
<i> This event is so boring.</i>

66
00:04:34,067 --> 00:04:35,567
<i> It's so quiet.</i>

67
00:04:35,700 --> 00:04:37,900
<i>Hotel bars are better than this.</i>

68
00:04:38,033 --> 00:04:39,600
<i> They have live bands.</i>

69
00:04:39,733 --> 00:04:41,033
<i> Do you want to come with me?</i>

70
00:04:41,167 --> 00:04:43,933
<i>Maybe you should make your voice
even sharper.</i>

71
00:04:44,067 --> 00:04:49,200
<i>You need more accent
because I can still hear Emma.</i>

72
00:04:51,100 --> 00:04:52,333
<i> Okay.</i>

73
00:04:52,467 --> 00:04:54,033
<i> Let's try again.</i>

74
00:04:56,533 --> 00:04:59,933
<i>Let's pretend I'm Danilo,
and you'll encounter me.</i>

75
00:05:04,467 --> 00:05:07,400
<i> Sorry, I didn't mean it.</i>

76
00:05:07,533 --> 00:05:09,967
<i> I'm in a rush.</i>

77
00:05:10,100 --> 00:05:14,267
<i>I'll move to a hotel bar
over there.</i>

78
00:05:14,400 --> 00:05:16,100
<i> Do you want to come with me?</i>

79
00:05:26,833 --> 00:05:27,800
<i> So?</i>

80
00:05:30,233 --> 00:05:31,300
<i> Is it still not good?</i>

81
00:05:33,500 --> 00:05:37,200
<i>Logan! What can you say?
Is that okay?</i>

82
00:05:40,567 --> 00:05:41,600
<i> Effective!</i>

83
00:05:41,733 --> 00:05:42,967
<i> That was good.</i>

84
00:05:43,100 --> 00:05:43,967
<i> Really?</i>

85
00:05:45,967 --> 00:05:50,000
<i>But how will we distract Jade
so I can get near Danilo?</i>

86
00:05:50,133 --> 00:05:53,100
<i> We'll give her this.</i>

87
00:05:53,233 --> 00:05:55,333
<i> What's that?</i>

88
00:05:55,467 --> 00:05:57,067
<i> Laxamatic.</i>

89
00:05:57,200 --> 00:05:59,000
<i> It's a mild laxative.</i>

90
00:05:59,133 --> 00:06:01,333
<i>Marco will put one on Jade's
drink.</i>

91
00:06:01,467 --> 00:06:04,533
<i>So we can help her use
the restroom...</i>

92
00:06:04,667 --> 00:06:05,967
<i> for hours.</i>

93
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:10,133
<i> And this...</i>

94
00:06:14,667 --> 00:06:16,600
<i> What's that for?</i>

95
00:06:16,733 --> 00:06:18,833
<i>I've used this perfume ever
since.</i>

96
00:06:18,967 --> 00:06:23,500
<i>This is cheap,
but Danilo loves its smell.</i>

97
00:06:23,633 --> 00:06:26,733
<i>Do you really have
to seduce Danilo?</i>

98
00:06:26,867 --> 00:06:29,600
<i>Isn't it Jade you're going
to haunt?</i>

99
00:06:29,733 --> 00:06:31,767
<i> She's our target, right?</i>

100
00:06:33,533 --> 00:06:38,033
<i>Logan, haven't we talked
about this already?</i>

101
00:06:38,167 --> 00:06:40,167
<i> Danilo is part of the plan.</i>

102
00:06:40,300 --> 00:06:44,667
<i>Jade must go crazy with
jealousy, just as she did to me.</i>

103
00:06:44,833 --> 00:06:45,967
<i> Okay.</i>

104
00:06:47,367 --> 00:06:48,233
All set.

105
00:06:48,367 --> 00:06:50,200
But let's split for now.

106
00:06:50,333 --> 00:06:53,967
Jade can't see us together,
especially me.

107
00:06:55,633 --> 00:06:56,500
Okay.

108
00:07:01,267 --> 00:07:06,467
At this point in my life,
I'm happy and contented.

109
00:07:06,600 --> 00:07:10,733
I'm slowly getting everything
I want to achieve.

110
00:07:10,867 --> 00:07:16,800
From my career to my personal
life.

111
00:07:28,967 --> 00:07:29,733
Love?

112
00:07:31,533 --> 00:07:34,400
Why are you looking
at that woman?

113
00:07:34,533 --> 00:07:37,700
She seems familiar to me.

114
00:07:37,833 --> 00:07:43,633
And she looked at us, too.
Don't we know her?

115
00:07:49,200 --> 00:07:51,467
<i> Yes, you look familiar.</i>

116
00:07:51,600 --> 00:07:54,600
<i>I have seen those gestures
before.</i>

117
00:08:00,467 --> 00:08:02,133
You know, you're so hot.

118
00:08:02,533 --> 00:08:03,600
It's like...

119
00:08:03,733 --> 00:08:04,867
unfair levels.

120
00:08:07,167 --> 00:08:08,767
You're a threat to guys.

121
00:08:11,833 --> 00:08:15,100
I haven't seen you and Mookie
together in school lately.

122
00:08:16,333 --> 00:08:17,833
Are you avoiding her?

123
00:08:19,133 --> 00:08:20,933
Can we not talk about her?

124
00:08:22,100 --> 00:08:23,367
Sorry.

125
00:08:24,400 --> 00:08:25,300
You know what?

126
00:08:25,433 --> 00:08:27,400
I find her strange.

127
00:08:27,533 --> 00:08:29,233
She's so weird.

128
00:08:29,367 --> 00:08:32,767
Do you see how she picks
a fight with me and my friends?

129
00:08:32,900 --> 00:08:37,067
Stacy, she's just fighting back
because you're bullying her.

130
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:40,400
Come on, it's just playful
pranks.

131
00:08:41,667 --> 00:08:44,967
But we should really avoid her.

132
00:08:45,100 --> 00:08:47,333
She's giving psycho vibes.

133
00:08:49,033 --> 00:08:56,200
Maybe her mom left because
she couldn't stand her daughter.

134
00:08:56,367 --> 00:08:59,500
Mookie's so evil.

135
00:08:59,633 --> 00:09:01,233
Even her mother can no longer
take her.

136
00:09:01,367 --> 00:09:02,967
Stop it, Stacy!

137
00:09:03,100 --> 00:09:06,600
You don't know Mookie
the way I know her.

138
00:09:06,733 --> 00:09:08,300
She's a good person.

139
00:09:08,433 --> 00:09:10,133
Don't judge her.

140
00:09:10,267 --> 00:09:12,800
Oh, please, Zayn!

141
00:09:12,933 --> 00:09:14,900
Stop defending her.

142
00:09:15,033 --> 00:09:17,367
Mookie is a walking red flag.

143
00:09:20,500 --> 00:09:22,500
You know?
I'll just use the restroom.

144
00:09:22,633 --> 00:09:23,900
BRB.

145
00:09:51,867 --> 00:09:53,267
Emma, don't stay there.

146
00:09:53,400 --> 00:09:54,600
You're so near to Jade.

147
00:09:54,733 --> 00:09:56,100
Go to the other side.

148
00:09:56,233 --> 00:09:57,700
Okay, okay.

149
00:09:59,033 --> 00:10:00,700
Excuse me.

150
00:10:00,833 --> 00:10:04,233
I'm just gonna say hi
to an old acquaintance.

151
00:10:05,933 --> 00:10:08,633
Looks like Jade is going
to approach you, Emma.

152
00:10:10,333 --> 00:10:11,600
That can't happen.

153
00:10:11,733 --> 00:10:14,167
I need to get near Danilo first.

154
00:10:14,300 --> 00:10:16,033
Oh my gosh, Miss Jade!

155
00:10:16,167 --> 00:10:18,333
I can't believe I'm seeing you
in person.

156
00:10:18,467 --> 00:10:20,733
Does the laxamatic take effect
already?

157
00:10:20,867 --> 00:10:23,033
It will take some time.

158
00:10:23,167 --> 00:10:24,933
Go to the other side for now.

159
00:10:25,067 --> 00:10:26,733
You'll get out of her sight.

160
00:10:26,867 --> 00:10:28,533
Okay.

161
00:10:28,667 --> 00:10:31,433
You know what? I'm a fan.
You're so beautiful!

162
00:10:31,567 --> 00:10:32,467
Thank you!

163
00:10:32,600 --> 00:10:34,567
Yes! You know what?
I love your products.

164
00:10:34,733 --> 00:10:39,533
I'm so amazed by how you
are as a person.

165
00:10:39,667 --> 00:10:41,600
- Oh my goodness, Miss Jade.
- I'm glad you loved it.

166
00:10:41,733 --> 00:10:43,633
I'm sure you're gonna
love Activora, too.

167
00:10:43,767 --> 00:10:45,667
- Thank you so much.
- Nice to see you.

168
00:10:45,800 --> 00:10:48,333
- Enjoy, enjoy the night. Bye.
- Thank you.

169
00:10:59,600 --> 00:11:00,767
Did I get out of Jade's sight?

170
00:11:02,033 --> 00:11:03,867
She's still looking for you.

171
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:05,500
Just keep avoiding her.

172
00:11:08,467 --> 00:11:12,567
Ladies and gentlemen,
the mind behind Activora...

173
00:11:12,700 --> 00:11:16,467
let's give a big round of
applause to Mrs. Ramirez!

174
00:11:23,300 --> 00:11:24,500
Go to Jade.

175
00:11:27,133 --> 00:11:29,000
Marco will help you.

176
00:11:29,133 --> 00:11:30,767
Yes, Amber.

177
00:11:30,900 --> 00:11:33,233
Yes, I'm with Zayn.

178
00:11:33,367 --> 00:11:35,800
It's so annoying.

179
00:11:35,933 --> 00:11:39,267
Zayn is still defending Mookie.

180
00:11:39,400 --> 00:11:43,200
That woman really takes after
her crazy mother.

181
00:11:43,367 --> 00:11:48,933
Anyway, wasn't her mom brought
to a mental facility?

182
00:11:49,067 --> 00:11:54,367
And she went wild
because she was crazy.

183
00:11:54,500 --> 00:11:58,200
And then she escaped
and abandoned Mookie.

184
00:11:58,333 --> 00:12:02,533
Oh my God, that family is so,
so weird.

185
00:12:03,867 --> 00:12:08,400
Oh my God!

186
00:12:08,533 --> 00:12:09,433
No!

187
00:12:09,567 --> 00:12:11,167
Oh my God!

188
00:12:16,833 --> 00:12:18,233
Hi, Miss.

189
00:12:18,367 --> 00:12:20,300
You again?

190
00:12:20,433 --> 00:12:21,800
Where's Miss Beautiful?

191
00:12:21,933 --> 00:12:24,233
The one you were with earlier.

192
00:12:25,667 --> 00:12:26,767
Freak.

193
00:12:29,967 --> 00:12:31,000
Mookie!

194
00:12:31,133 --> 00:12:32,367
I didn't know you were here.

195
00:12:32,500 --> 00:12:34,000
Can we please talk?

196
00:12:34,133 --> 00:12:35,000
Please?

197
00:12:35,133 --> 00:12:36,167
It won't take long.

198
00:12:36,300 --> 00:12:37,667
Sorry, Zayn. I need to go.

199
00:12:41,267 --> 00:12:42,733
Mooks, there's just something
I need to tell you.

200
00:12:51,500 --> 00:12:52,200
Zayn!

201
00:12:52,333 --> 00:12:53,933
Hey. What happened to you?

202
00:12:54,067 --> 00:12:55,233
Someone threw trash at me.

203
00:12:55,367 --> 00:12:56,400
- I don't know who.
- What?

204
00:12:56,533 --> 00:12:58,100
I need to go home.

205
00:13:07,433 --> 00:13:09,600
Good evening, everyone.

206
00:13:09,733 --> 00:13:13,533
Welcome to the launch
of Ramirez Laboratory

207
00:13:13,667 --> 00:13:18,100
and Artemis Pharmacy's newest
life-changing multi-vitamins.

208
00:13:18,233 --> 00:13:20,867
- from sunrise to sundown.
- Jade doesn't stop.

209
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:22,800
Did she see me?

210
00:13:22,967 --> 00:13:25,867
Emma, she's looking in your
direction.

211
00:13:30,633 --> 00:13:35,033
I'm on my way there.
I'm gonna stop her.

212
00:13:35,167 --> 00:13:37,000
Emma, she's on her way to you.

213
00:13:37,133 --> 00:13:38,433
Gotcha.

214
00:13:43,800 --> 00:13:45,400
Don't turn around, Emma.

215
00:13:49,700 --> 00:13:50,900
- I'll go to you.
- Excuse me.

216
00:13:54,100 --> 00:13:56,267
Boss, it's dangerous.

217
00:13:56,433 --> 00:13:59,800
She might notice that you're
keeping her away from Emma.

218
00:13:59,933 --> 00:14:00,900
Hi!

219
00:14:01,033 --> 00:14:04,567
I'm Jade Caparas
of Artemis Pharmacy.

220
00:14:04,700 --> 00:14:06,633
The partner of Ramirez Lab.

221
00:14:06,767 --> 00:14:07,833
And you are?

222
00:14:10,333 --> 00:14:11,100
Hi!

223
00:14:11,233 --> 00:14:13,700
I'm Jade Caparas
of Artemis Pharmacy.

224
00:14:14,767 --> 00:14:16,600
The partner of Ramirez Lab.

225
00:14:16,733 --> 00:14:17,900
And you are?

226
00:14:20,500 --> 00:14:21,167
Boss.

227
00:14:22,700 --> 00:14:24,900
- It's risky.
- May I call on Jade Caparas...

228
00:14:25,033 --> 00:14:29,200
the brilliant woman behind
this spectacular launch.

229
00:14:42,300 --> 00:14:44,800
Thank you, Mrs. Ramirez.

230
00:14:44,933 --> 00:14:47,000
Thank you so much.

231
00:14:47,133 --> 00:14:48,400
Hello.

232
00:14:51,133 --> 00:14:52,267
Hello, Mister.

233
00:14:53,300 --> 00:14:54,967
Are you almost here?

234
00:14:55,100 --> 00:14:57,833
Yes, I'm already outside.

235
00:14:57,967 --> 00:14:59,067
Okay.

236
00:15:02,867 --> 00:15:03,800
Mookie!

237
00:15:05,867 --> 00:15:07,500
You did this to me, didn't you?

238
00:15:07,633 --> 00:15:08,567
What are you talking about?

239
00:15:08,700 --> 00:15:09,467
And you're denying it!

240
00:15:09,600 --> 00:15:11,967
You poured trash on me,
didn't you?

241
00:15:12,100 --> 00:15:13,067
You have no proof.

242
00:15:13,200 --> 00:15:14,100
Oh, really?

243
00:15:14,233 --> 00:15:15,900
You're the only one
who hates me.

244
00:15:16,033 --> 00:15:17,333
You're the only one
who can do this!

245
00:15:17,467 --> 00:15:18,233
Stacy, stop!

246
00:15:19,667 --> 00:15:20,700
Let go of me!

247
00:15:22,600 --> 00:15:24,133
Is it true, Mookie?

248
00:15:24,267 --> 00:15:26,400
Did you pour trash on Stacy?

249
00:15:28,233 --> 00:15:29,467
Fine.

250
00:15:29,600 --> 00:15:30,433
I did.

251
00:15:30,567 --> 00:15:31,600
You're so evil!

252
00:15:31,733 --> 00:15:33,033
Stacy, come on! That's enough!

253
00:15:33,167 --> 00:15:35,033
The nerve of you
to call me evil.

254
00:15:35,200 --> 00:15:37,300
Stacy, I just got even with you.

255
00:15:37,433 --> 00:15:38,100
Mookie, enough!

256
00:15:38,233 --> 00:15:39,700
Can you please stop?

257
00:15:39,833 --> 00:15:41,000
You're way out of line!

258
00:15:41,133 --> 00:15:42,000
Stacy, stop!

259
00:15:43,867 --> 00:15:46,733
How dare you call me
the bad guy here.

260
00:15:46,867 --> 00:15:50,633
Let me remind you of all the
bullying you did to me before.

261
00:15:50,767 --> 00:15:52,367
You and your friends.

262
00:15:52,500 --> 00:15:55,100
So, suffer from it.

263
00:15:56,233 --> 00:15:57,300
Stay here, Stacy.

264
00:15:57,433 --> 00:15:58,400
Let her be!

265
00:15:58,533 --> 00:15:59,333
Stay here.

266
00:15:59,467 --> 00:16:00,667
Let go of me!

267
00:16:02,133 --> 00:16:03,767
Where are you going, Zayn?

268
00:16:11,633 --> 00:16:13,200
Hello, Tyler?

269
00:16:13,333 --> 00:16:14,367
Where are you?

270
00:16:15,733 --> 00:16:17,233
I need help.

271
00:16:18,567 --> 00:16:25,033
The true credit belongs
to my twin sister, Olive.

272
00:16:26,800 --> 00:16:29,200
It was Olive's dream...

273
00:16:29,333 --> 00:16:31,067
her belief...

274
00:16:31,200 --> 00:16:34,800
that Activora will not be just
any other supplements.

275
00:16:34,933 --> 00:16:39,567
But instead, it's going
to be a daily promise.

276
00:16:40,633 --> 00:16:45,100
A habit that will empower
us to live a healthier

277
00:16:45,267 --> 00:16:50,133
and stronger lifestyle
for those we love,

278
00:16:50,267 --> 00:16:56,200
for our families, and for the
love of our lives.

279
00:16:59,267 --> 00:17:00,933
Thank you so much for coming,

280
00:17:01,067 --> 00:17:03,167
and enjoy the rest of the
evening.

281
00:17:19,000 --> 00:17:21,100
- Thank you for being here.
- Emma?

282
00:17:21,233 --> 00:17:22,233
Thank you so much.

283
00:17:22,367 --> 00:17:23,267
Thank you for your support.

284
00:17:23,400 --> 00:17:27,000
Danilo, did you mention Emma's
name?

285
00:17:27,133 --> 00:17:30,567
The woman who passed by seemed
to be wearing

286
00:17:30,700 --> 00:17:32,267
the same perfume Emma
used to wear.

287
00:17:32,400 --> 00:17:34,133
The baby cologne she uses.

288
00:17:34,267 --> 00:17:35,633
Are you serious?

289
00:17:35,767 --> 00:17:37,333
This place is so classy.

290
00:17:37,467 --> 00:17:39,533
And someone here uses
a baby cologne?

291
00:17:40,933 --> 00:17:42,167
What's happening?

292
00:17:44,933 --> 00:17:47,467
Don't ask.
It'll put you in a bad mood.

293
00:17:48,867 --> 00:17:49,967
It's nothing, Jade.

294
00:17:51,033 --> 00:17:52,167
It's nothing, right?

295
00:17:55,133 --> 00:17:57,400
What's going on, Leticia?

296
00:17:57,533 --> 00:18:04,767
Danilo said a woman who passed
by smelled like Emma.

297
00:18:05,967 --> 00:18:07,867
Where is she?

298
00:18:08,000 --> 00:18:09,200
Right there.

299
00:18:29,267 --> 00:18:30,667
- Mookie!
- What's taking them so long?

300
00:18:33,500 --> 00:18:35,433
What are you doing here, Zayn?

301
00:18:35,567 --> 00:18:38,967
Are you here to tell me again
that I'm evil?

302
00:18:40,433 --> 00:18:43,533
You know very well
that Stacy is the evil one.

303
00:18:43,667 --> 00:18:45,967
She's so good at bullying.

304
00:18:46,100 --> 00:18:49,400
And now that I fight back,
she plays the victim?

305
00:18:49,533 --> 00:18:53,667
Don't you remember when
I was on a wheelchair?

306
00:18:53,800 --> 00:18:56,267
Didn't she and her friends
toyed with me?

307
00:19:02,367 --> 00:19:03,300
What are you doing?

308
00:19:05,800 --> 00:19:08,367
Bring her back here! I'm not yet
done!

309
00:19:08,500 --> 00:19:09,867
But it's okay.

310
00:19:10,767 --> 00:19:13,733
I learned to fight back
because of that.

311
00:19:13,867 --> 00:19:17,400
Mooks, I admire you for being
brave.

312
00:19:17,533 --> 00:19:19,667
And for defending yourself.

313
00:19:19,800 --> 00:19:21,567
But what you did to Stacy...

314
00:19:21,700 --> 00:19:23,033
You started it.

315
00:19:23,167 --> 00:19:25,033
She didn't provoke you.

316
00:19:25,167 --> 00:19:27,000
What do you mean she didn't
provoke me?

317
00:19:28,100 --> 00:19:31,467
She said mean things
about my mom.

318
00:19:31,600 --> 00:19:33,667
Fine!

319
00:19:33,800 --> 00:19:36,433
She can mistreat or bully me all
she wants.

320
00:19:36,567 --> 00:19:37,667
Because I can fight.

321
00:19:37,800 --> 00:19:39,600
But she must not dragged
my mom into this

322
00:19:39,733 --> 00:19:42,233
because she can't protect
herself.

323
00:19:43,233 --> 00:19:43,567
You know what?

324
00:19:45,167 --> 00:19:46,167
Just go home.

325
00:19:46,300 --> 00:19:47,967
Leave me alone, Zayn.

326
00:19:48,100 --> 00:19:50,833
You don't want to have anything
to do with me, anyway. Right?

327
00:19:50,967 --> 00:19:52,567
Fine, I said that.

328
00:19:53,167 --> 00:19:54,933
But it's easier said than done.

329
00:19:55,767 --> 00:19:56,467
Look.

330
00:19:57,400 --> 00:19:59,000
We need to talk.

331
00:19:59,133 --> 00:20:01,533
I'm no longer happy with
what's happening to us.

332
00:20:01,700 --> 00:20:04,000
I'm not used to us being like
this.

333
00:20:04,133 --> 00:20:05,200
We're always fighting.

334
00:20:05,333 --> 00:20:06,867
Leave me alone.

335
00:20:12,167 --> 00:20:14,700
- Mookie.
- Thank you. You can go now.

336
00:20:14,833 --> 00:20:15,900
Okay.

337
00:20:47,900 --> 00:20:51,667
Tyler, Zed, go get Mookie.

338
00:20:51,800 --> 00:20:53,533
You're good at this, right?

339
00:20:53,667 --> 00:20:55,433
Bring her to me.

340
00:20:55,567 --> 00:20:56,533
Wait.

341
00:20:56,667 --> 00:20:58,800
Won't we get in trouble
for this?

342
00:20:58,933 --> 00:21:01,467
She won't recognize you.

343
00:21:01,600 --> 00:21:04,167
We'll just scare her.

344
00:21:04,300 --> 00:21:06,200
Go. You can do it.

345
00:21:07,733 --> 00:21:09,233
- Come on.
- Let's wear this.

346
00:21:16,033 --> 00:21:17,033
Be quiet.

347
00:21:33,433 --> 00:21:34,600
Jade, what's the matter?

348
00:21:34,733 --> 00:21:35,467
What's wrong?

349
00:21:35,600 --> 00:21:36,700
Do you want medicine?

350
00:21:36,833 --> 00:21:37,367
I'll get it in the car.

351
00:21:37,500 --> 00:21:38,800
No, no, no. I'm fine.

352
00:21:40,667 --> 00:21:42,167
Maybe this is just an upset
stomach.

353
00:21:42,333 --> 00:21:44,700
I ate a lot of greasy food
earlier.

354
00:21:46,433 --> 00:21:47,133
I'll go with you.

355
00:21:47,267 --> 00:21:48,600
- Come on.
- Yes, please. Yes, yes.

356
00:21:48,733 --> 00:21:50,300
Love, we'll just go to
the restroom real quick.

357
00:21:50,433 --> 00:21:52,100
Leticia, please come with me.

358
00:22:00,367 --> 00:22:02,300
It has taken effect, Emma.

359
00:22:02,433 --> 00:22:04,800
It's your time to shine.

360
00:22:04,933 --> 00:22:06,533
You can attack now.

361
00:22:23,267 --> 00:22:24,233
Zayn?

362
00:22:29,867 --> 00:22:30,967
Zayn?

363
00:22:41,433 --> 00:22:43,267
Help!

364
00:23:33,100 --> 00:23:34,800
Are you following me?

365
00:23:39,967 --> 00:23:41,400
It's okay.

366
00:23:41,533 --> 00:23:44,467
I've been feeling bored.

367
00:23:44,600 --> 00:23:46,533
I want someone to talk to.

368
00:23:53,367 --> 00:23:54,833
You like me, right?

369
00:23:57,767 --> 00:23:59,667
Not really.

370
00:23:59,800 --> 00:24:01,500
Your voice sounds familiar.

371
00:24:01,633 --> 00:24:05,100
I thought you were my wife,
Emma.

372
00:24:06,767 --> 00:24:10,767
He still treats me as his wife
after replacing me with Jade.

373
00:24:23,400 --> 00:24:28,567
I believe I have the right to be
happy with the person I love.

374
00:24:28,700 --> 00:24:30,167
And that's Danilo.

375
00:24:30,333 --> 00:24:32,367
How long was Emma gone for you

376
00:24:32,500 --> 00:24:33,833
to replace her with another
woman?

377
00:24:33,967 --> 00:24:37,400
Are you sure she will never
return?

378
00:24:37,533 --> 00:24:39,700
Let's not talk about her.

379
00:24:39,833 --> 00:24:42,433
Because I want to forget her.

380
00:24:42,567 --> 00:24:44,800
Does it need to reach
that point?

381
00:24:44,933 --> 00:24:47,200
She's getting carried away
by her emotions.

382
00:24:47,333 --> 00:24:47,933
Oh my!

383
00:24:48,067 --> 00:24:49,533
Look!

384
00:24:49,667 --> 00:24:50,533
What?

385
00:24:50,667 --> 00:24:53,067
I've been away for a short
while,

386
00:24:53,200 --> 00:24:56,300
and someone already wants
to steal my fiancé.
